{{Infobox sport tournament | name = 1966 Basque Pelota World Championships | image = 1966 Basque Pelota World Championships poster.png | caption = Tournament poster | location = {{flagicon|Uruguay}} [[Montevideo]], [[Uruguay]] | start_date = December | end_date = | administrator = [[International Federation of Basque Pelota|FIPV]] | tournament_format = | venues = | teams = 7+ | purse = | champions = {{flag|France}} | runners-up1 = {{flag|Mexico}} | runners-up2 = {{flag|Spain}} | matches = | points = | attendance = | previous = [[1962 Basque Pelota World Championships|1962]] | next = [[1970 Basque Pelota World Championships|1970]] | website = }}
The '''1966 Basque Pelota World Championships''' were the 5th edition of the [[Basque Pelota World Championships]] organized by the [[International Federation of Basque Pelota|FIPV]].
==Participating nations== {{col-begin|width=70%}} {{col-break}} *{{flag|Argentina}} *{{flag|Chile}} *{{flag|Cuba}} {{col-break}} *{{flag|France}} *{{flag|Mexico}} *{{flag|Spain}} {{col-break}} *{{flag|Uruguay}} *Others {{col-end}}
==Events== A total of 12 events were disputed, in 4 playing areas.<ref>{{cite web| author=Javier Solano| title=Historia de los Mundiales| date=November 2004| language=Spanish| url=http://fipv.net/images/historial/MUNDIALES_1952-1998.pdf#page=17| accessdate=20 September 2016}}</ref>
