{{Infobox ice hockey team season |League=NHL |Season=1969–70 |year=1969 |Team=Oakland Seals |Division= [[West Division (NHL)|West]] |DivisionRank= 4th |Record= 22–40–14 |HomeRecord= |RoadRecord= |GoalsFor= 169 |GoalsAgainst= 243 |GeneralManager= [[Frank Selke Jr.]] |Coach= [[Fred Glover (ice hockey)|Fred Glover]] |Captain= [[Ted Hampson]] |AltCaptain= |Arena= Oakland-Alameda County Coliseum Arena |Attendance= |GoalsLeader= [[Carol Vadnais]] (24) |AssistsLeader= Ted Hampson (35) |PointsLeader= Ted Hampson (52) |PIMLeader= Carol Vadnais (212) |WinsLeader= [[Gary Smith (ice hockey)|Gary Smith]] (19) |GAALeader= Gary Smith (3.11) |next_season=[[1970–71 California Golden Seals season|1970–71]] }}
The '''[[1969–70 NHL season|1969–70]] [[Oakland Seals]] season''' was the Seals' third [[season (sports)|season]] in the [[NHL]]. They qualified for the [[Stanley Cup]] [[NHL playoffs|playoffs]] for the second year in a row, and were again eliminated in the first round. It was the last time the Seals qualified for the playoffs.
