==Championship Final==
The Vancouver Island Crimson Tide (Western Division champions) defeated the Toronto Renegades (Eastern Division Champions) 23-11 in the Championship Final, played in [[Duncan, British Columbia]] on 24 July 1999.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/thestar/access/427824111.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Jul+26%2C+1999&author=&pub=Toronto+Star&desc=Big+debut+for+sisters&pqatl=google|title=Big debut for sisters|publisher=[[Toronto Star]]|date=1999-07-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rugbycanada.ca/news/super_final_99.htm|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20000301232549/http://www.rugbycanada.ca/news/super_final_99.htm|title=Crimson Tide Win Second National Super League Title|archivedate=2000-03-01|accessdate=2011-04-24|publisher=[[Rugby Canada]]}}</ref>
