{{infobox country at games | NOC = HKG | NOCname = [[Sports Federation and Olympic Committee of Hong Kong]] | games = Summer Olympics | year = 1952 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.hkolympic.org }}&nbsp;{{zh icon}} {{en icon}} | location = [[Helsinki]] | competitors = 4 | sports = 1 | flagbearer = Volunteer | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
'''[[Hong Kong]]''' competed in the [[Summer Olympic Games]] for the first time at the '''[[1952 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Helsinki]], [[Finland]].
Four athletes competed four Hong Kong, and a non-participant served as flag-bearer for the Hong Kong delegation at the opening ceremony.<ref>{{cite news|title=15th Olympic Games Opened as 70,000 See Rites in Rain|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=AMAcAAAAIBAJ&sjid=X34EAAAAIBAJ&pg=6824%2C1202691|accessdate=12 August 2016|publisher=The Milwaukee Journal|date=19 July 1952|quote=Hong Kong sent a flagbearer and four athletes}}</ref>
==Athletes==
* [[Francisco Xavier Monteiro]] (1926 [[Hong Kong]]-?) ** Men's 100 m Freestyle ** Men's 400 m Freestyle ** 1500 m Freestyle * [[Kin Man Cheung]] (1932 [[Borneo]] -?) ** Men's 100 m Freestyle ** Men's 400 m Freestyle ** 1500 m Freestyle * [[Cynthia Eager]] (1936 [[Hong Kong]]-?) * Women's 100 m Freestyle * Women's 400 m Freestyle * [[Irene Anita Kwok Kam Ngor]] (1933 [[Hong Kong]]-?) * Women's 200 m Breaststroke
