{{Orphan|date=February 2013}}
'''Mehari Shinash''' is an [[Eritrea]]n [[Association football|footballer]]. He played for the [[Eritrea national football team]].
==International career== Shinash played in the [[2009 CECAFA Cup]] in [[Kenya]], where his cross was deflected in for an [[own goal]] in the 3-1 victory against [[Somalia national football team|Somalia]].<ref name="standard-somalia">{{Cite news|url=http://www.standardmedia.co.ke/InsidePage.php?id=1144029771&cid=38& |title=Eritrea crush Somalia as Rwanda pip Zims |date=6 December 2009 |work=The Standard |accessdate=15 December 2009|location=Nairobi }}</ref>
==Personal life== He was born from an Ethiopian father and an Eritrean mother in Asmara, Eritrea. Whilst competing in the [[2009 CECAFA Cup]] in [[Kenya]] he was part of the [[Eritrea national football team]] which failed to return home after competing in the regional tournament in [[Nairobi]].<ref>http://edition.cnn.com/2009/SPORT/football/12/15/football.cecafa.eritrea.kenya/index.html 12 Eritrean soccer players sought in Kenya</ref> After receiving refugee status from the Australian government, the team moved to [[Adelaide]], [[Australia]].<ref>http://www.adelaidenow.com.au/sport/out-of-africa-its-a-whole-new-ball-game/story-e6frecj3-1226036645661 Out of Africa, it's a whole new ball game </ref>
