{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Mohan Meakins Cricket Stadium | nickname = | fullname = Mohan Meakins Cricket Stadium | former_names = Narendra Mohan Sports Stadium | caption = | country = [[India]] | location = [[Ghaziabad, India|Ghaziabad]], [[Uttar Pradesh]] | establishment = 1971 | Floodlight = No | seating_capacity = 200 | owner = [[Government of Uttar Pradesh]] | operator = [[Uttar Pradesh Cricket Association]] | tenants = [[Uttar Pradesh cricket team]] | source = http://www.espncricinfo.com/india/content/ground/58090.html cricinfo }} '''Mohan Meakins Cricket Stadium''' or '''Narendra Mohan Sports Stadium''' is a cricket ground in [[Ghaziabad, India|Ghaziabad]], [[India]]. The stadium has hosted 12 [[Ranji]] matches from 1977 when home team [[Uttar Pradesh cricket team]] and [[Baroda cricket team]] played other. The ground was also host 1977/78 [[Ranji Trophy]] finals featuring [[Uttar Pradesh cricket team]] and [[Karnataka cricket team]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/1136_f.html First-class Matches]</ref>
The stadium one of 25 venue for [[1997 Women's Cricket World Cup]] and hosted two matches between [[Netherlands women's national cricket team|Netherlands Women's]] and [[New Zealand women's national cricket team|New Zealand Women's]]<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/64/64982.html Scoredcard]</ref> and again between [[India women's national cricket team|India Women's]] and [[Netherlands women's national cricket team|Netherlands Women's]]<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/65/65014.html Scoredcard]</ref>
