{{Infobox stadium | name = Parque Palermo | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | caption = | fullname = | former_names = | location = | coordinates = {{Coord|34|53|52.31|S|56|9|12.80|W|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = {{Start date|1937|10|31}} | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Central Español]] | operator = | surface = grass | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 6,500 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | tenants = [[Central Español]] | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }}
'''Parque Palermo''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Montevideo]], [[Uruguay]]. It is currently used primarily for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and is the home stadium of [[Central Español]]. The stadium holds 6,500 spectators.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldstadiums.com/south_america/countries/uruguay.shtml |title=Stadiums in Uruguay|publisher=Worldstadiums.com|accessdate=12 September 2011}}</ref> Parque Palermo is located within [[Parque Batlle]], close to the [[Estadio Centenario]] and the [[Parque Luis Méndez Piana]].
