{{Infobox rugby league biography |name = Patrick Herbert |fullname = |nickname = |image = |image_size = |position = {{rlp|CE|FB|WG}} | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1997|1|10|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Whakatane, New Zealand]] | height = {{convert|1.81|m|abbr=on}} | weight = {{convert|94|kg|stlb|abbr=on}} | club1 = [[St. George Illawarra Dragons|St. George Illawarra]] | year1start = 2018 | year1end = present | appearances1 = 0 | tries1 = 0 | goals1 = 0 | fieldgoals1 = 0 | points1 = 0 |new = yes }}
'''Patrick Herbert''' is a New Zealand rugby league footballer who plays for the [[St George Illawarra Dragons]] in the [[NRL]]. He primarily plays as a {{rlp|ce}}.
==Background== Herbert was born in [[Whakatane]], [[New Zealand]]. He played junior rugby union for the Tamaki Rugby Club. In 2015 he made the switch to rugby league and signed with the [[St. George Illawarra Dragons]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theleader.com.au/story/3450837/dragons-sign-former-roosters-player-taane-milne-and-under-20s-patrick-herbert/|title=Dragons sign former Roosters player Taane Milne and under 20s Patrick Herbert|last=Haigh|first=Paul|date=2015-10-27|work=St George & Sutherland Shire Leader|access-date=2018-08-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180722213530/https://www.theleader.com.au/story/3450837/dragons-sign-former-roosters-player-taane-milne-and-under-20s-patrick-herbert/|archive-date=2018-07-22|dead-url=no|publisher=Fairfax Media|language=en|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nswrl.com.au/news/2018/05/13/new-fullback-herbert-happy-with-dragons-reshuffle/|title=New Fullback Herbert Happy with Dragons Reshuffle|last=Masterson|first=Simon|date=2018-05-13|work=New South Wales Rugby League|access-date=2018-07-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180730081029/https://www.nswrl.com.au/news/2018/05/13/new-fullback-herbert-happy-with-dragons-reshuffle/|archive-date=2018-07-30|dead-url=no|publisher=National Rugby League|language=en-AU|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nswrl.com.au/news/2018/06/02/report-north-sydney-v-st-george-illawarra/|title=Field And Herbert Star In Dragons Win|last=Cupido|first=Andre|date=2018-06-02|work=New South Wales Rugby League|access-date=2018-07-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180730081149/https://www.nswrl.com.au/news/2018/06/02/report-north-sydney-v-st-george-illawarra/|archive-date=2018-07-30|dead-url=no|publisher=National Rugby League|language=en-AU|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In 2016 he re-signed with the Dragons, keeping him with the club until at least the end of 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dragons.com.au/news/2016/06/02/herbert-re-signs-with-dragons/|title=Herbert Re-Signs With Dragons|last=|first=|date=2016-06-02|work=St George Illawarra Dragons|access-date=2018-08-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180326225248/https://www.dragons.com.au/news/2016/06/02/herbert-re-signs-with-dragons/|archive-date=2018-03-26|dead-url=no|publisher=National Rugby League|language=en-AU|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
